            2020</ref>)<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></sourceNote><content class="align_justified first_line_indent_18"><inline class="small_caps">By His
                Excellency Sir DAVID CLIVE
                WILSON</inline>,
            Knight Commander of the Most Distinguished Order of Saint Michael and Saint George,
            Governor and Commander-in-Chief of Hong
            Kong.<marker role="blank-line"></marker></content><content class="align_justified first_line_indent_18">In exercise of the powers conferred on
            me by <ref>section 5(1)(e)</ref> of the Inland Revenue Ordinance, <ref href="/hk/cap112">Chapter 112</ref>, I hereby PROCLAIM that, in respect of the year
            of assessment commencing on 1 April 1988, and subsequent years of assessment, property
            tax shall be charged in respect of land or buildings or land and buildings in Area T as
            defined in the <ref>Schedule</ref> to the Rating (Areas of Hong Kong)
            Order*.<marker role="blank-line"></marker></content><content class="align_justified first_line_indent_18">G<inline class="small_caps">iven</inline> under my hand and the Public Seal this 5th day of
            December
            1987.<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></content><content><table xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" width="400">
